    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Corrections</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Feb 26 article about declining share of income paid in taxes by wealthiest Americans misstated share of all federal income taxes paid by top one percent of taxpayers in 1998; it was 34.75 percent; 18.5 percent was their share of total individual income</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>An article in Business Day on Monday about the declining share of income paid in taxes by the wealthiest Americans misstated the share of all federal income taxes paid by the top 1 percent of taxpayers in 1998. It was 34.75 percent; 18.5 percent was their share of total individual income.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>An article in Business Day on Monday about the declining share of income paid in taxes by the wealthiest Americans misstated the share of all federal income taxes paid by the top 1 percent of taxpayers in 1998. It was 34.75 percent; 18.5 percent was their share of total individual income.</p>
      </block>
